{
  "text": "Cell morphology was observed under a light microscope with phase-contrast optics (magnification 4006) (Olympus). Motility was assayed using a semi-solid BSW-3 agar tube supplemented with 0.3 % agar. Cells were inoculated by stabbing with a straight needle and the tube was incubated at 25 u C for 7 days. Cell preparations were made by rapid freezing and the freeze substitution method described by [CITATION_1] with slight modification. The ultrathin sections were stained with uranyl acetate and lead citrate, then observed in a transmission electron microscope (Tecnai 20; FEI) at an acceleration voltage of 120 kV (Fig. 2a) . Additionally, the external structure of cells of strain TAR-002",
